Function Reference/the author aim « WordPress Codex
-----------

This tag displays the **A**OL **I**nstant **M**essenger screenname for
the author of a post. The **AIM** field is set in the user's profile
([Administration](/Administration_Panels "Administration Panels") \>
[Profile](/Administration_Panels#Your_Profile "Administration Panels")
\> [Your Profile](/Your_Profile_SubPanel "Your Profile SubPanel")). This
tag must be used within [The Loop](/The_Loop "The Loop").

Replace With
------------

-   [the\_author\_meta('aim')](/Template_Tags/the_author_meta "Template Tags/the author meta")

Usage
-----

`  <?php the_author_aim(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Example
-------

    <p>Contact me on AOL Instant Messenger: <?php the_author_aim(); ?></p>

Change Log
----------

-   Since: 0.71
-   Deprecated: 2.8.0
-   Replace By:
    [the\_author\_meta('aim')](/Template_Tags/the_author_meta "Template Tags/the author meta")

